### **Project Overview**

SauceDemo is a sample e-commerce web application used for automation testing and training. The purpose of this BRS is to outline the functional and non-functional requirements for the QA validation of SauceDemo as a standard user-facing shopping platform.

### **Objective**

Ensure that SauceDemo functions as expected under defined business rules and scenarios and is thoroughly validated for performance, usability, and reliability.

# **Scope**

Testing will cover:

* User authentication (login/logout)  
* Product listing & sorting  
* Shopping cart operations  
* Checkout process  
* Order confirmation  
* Error handling


### **Stakeholders**

| Stakeholder | Role |
| :---- | ----- |
| QA Analyst | Responsible for test case design, execution, defect reporting |
| Developer | Fix issues and deliver working builds |
| Product Owner | Ensures feature completeness and alignment with user needs   |

### 

### 

### 

### **Functional Requirements**

| ID |  Requirement | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| FR-1 | User Login | User must be able to log in using valid credentials |
| FR-2 | Invalid Login | Error message must appear on invalid login attempt |
| FR-3 | Product Display | Products should be listed with name, price, and image |
| FR-4 | Product Sorting | Users should be able to sort products by price/name |
| FR-5 | Add to Cart | User should be able to add items to the cart |
| FR-6 | Remove from Cart | User should be able to remove items from the cart |
| FR-7 | Checkout | User can enter information and complete purchase |
| FR-8 | Order Confirmation | Confirmation message after successful checkout |

### **Non-Functional Requirements**

| ID | Requirement | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| NFR-1 | Performance | Pages should load within 3 seconds |
| NFR-2 | Compatibility | Application must work on Chrome, Firefox, Edge |
| NFR-3 | Usability | UI should be clean, consistent, and accessible |
| NFR-4 | Security | Password should not be displayed in plain text |
| NFR-5 | Reliability | Application should not crash during any valid scenario |
| NFR-6 | Accessibility | Basic keyboard navigation and readable text must be ensured |

### **Key Assumptions**

* ## User data is mocked and not stored permanently.

* ## Environment will remain stable during testing cycles.

### **Items Not in Scope**

* Payment gateway integration  
* Backend database validation

### **QA Deliverables**

* Test Plan  
* Test Scenarios & Test Cases  
* Bug Reports with screenshots  
* Test Summary Report

### **Conclusion**

This BRS outlines the QA validation process for the SauceDemo application. It ensures that all key business functionalities and quality standards are met. 

The document will guide the QA team in executing both manual and automated testing using Playwright, Selenium, and Postman to deliver a reliable and user-friendly application.
